    • Method Detail

      • getMapChoice

        protected java.lang.String getMapChoice()
        A method that creates a list of the files in the root folder, filters so that only '.txt. files are added to the list and retrieves the names of the maps from their respective text files and added to an arrayList. The map names are then printed and the user is asked to select a map. This map choice is taken and rounded to the nearest available map e.g. if you enter 6 and there are only 4 maps, the fourth map will be chosen. The program will print a message to confirm the user's selection and return the file name.
        Returns:
        fileName String - A string containing the file name of the map that has been chosen by the user and therefore the name of the file to be read

      • readMap

        protected void readMap​(java.lang.String fileName)
        A method that reads the map from the specified file and saves it to the 2 dimension array list allowing it to be accessed through the object
        Parameters:
        fileName - String - A string containing the name of the file of the chosen map to be read.
